Kashif Inayat



(Doctorate Fellow Researcher at Incheon National University, South Korea)

CV (2 June, 2020)

Google Scholar

Linkedin

Github

Biography:

Kashif Inayat currently working as a doctorate fellow researcher at System-on-Chips (SoC) Laboratory, Electronics Engineering Department of Incheon National University, South Korea. He consider himself fortunate to have the opportunity to work under Prof. Jaeyong Chung at Incheon National University. Furthermore, he completed his Master of Science in Electronics and Computer Engineering (ECE) from graduate school, Hongik University in 2019 under supervision of Prof. Seong Oun Hwang. And received his Bachelor's degree in Electronic Engineering from Iqra University Ismabad Campus, Pakistan under supervision of Prof. Viqar Ahmed in 2014. After completing undergrad degree, he worked at Computing and Technology Department, Iqra University as a Lab Engineer for 2.7 years. Moreover, during MS studies he worked at Information Security and Machine Learning Lab, Hongik University, South Korea as a graduate researcher for 2.5 years. Furthermore, he chaired the special sessions at International Conference on Green and Human Information Technology (ICGHIT 2019), held at Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia (Jan, 16-18, 2019). Moreover, he is the registered member of Pakistan Engineering Council and reviewer for the IEEE Access Journal.

Area of Interest:

His research interests include neuromorphic systems (more specifically Systolic Arrays, TPU's & Accelerators). However, in MS studies he focused on Hardware Security, Asymmetric Cryptography, Post-Quantum Cryptography and blockchain. In a nutshell, like to work for efficient AI computing/architectures, application of asymmetric and code-based cryptographic schemes in embedded systems, blockchain and IoT's.
